ittabawassee river which runs within yards of dows main plant in midland were found to contain elevated levels of the cancercausing chemical dioxin in november  the dioxin was located in sediments two to ten feet below the surface of the river and according to the new york times there is no indication that residents or workers in the area are directly exposed to the sites however people who often eat fish from the river had slightly elevated levels of dioxin in their blood in july  dow reached an agreement with the environmental protection agency to remove  cubic yards  m of sediment from three areas of the riverbed and levees of the river that had been found to be contaminated in november  dow chemical along with the united states environmental protection agency and michigan department of environmental quality agreed to establish a superfund to address dioxin cleanup of the tittabawassee river saginaw river and saginaw bay sale of herbicide businessedit in december  dow chemicals agreed to sell its global herbicide business as low crop prices prompted consolidation in the agricultural sector environmental recordedit in  dow agreed to pay  million the largest penalty ever in a pesticide case to the state of new york for making illegal safety claims related to its pesticides the new york attorney generals office stated that dow agrosciences had violated a  agreement with the state of new york to stop advertisements making safety claims about its pesticide products dow stated that it was not admitting to any wrongdoing and that it was agreeing to the settlement to avoid a costly court battle according to the united states environmental protection agency epa dow has some responsibility for  of the united states superfund toxic waste sites placing it in th place by number of sitescitation needed one of these a former ucc uranium and vanadium processing facility near uravan colorado is listed as the sole responsibility of dow the rest are shared with numerous other compa